<div id="review_7938666" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/7938666" />
    <a title="Heidi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/454236-heidi"><img alt="Heidi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1422623715p2/454236.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/7938666?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heidi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heidi" href="/user/show/454236-heidi">Heidi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7938666" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17294842629949216462">Maybe this will make me look stupid... but this book was far too brainy, academic and philosophical to be a really engrossing read. I had to make myself slog through certain portions of this book -- Eco is clearly brilliant, but needs to learn to keep a plot together. Too much extraneous information, too many digressions, too much detailed background information, and you distract from the plot.<br/><br/>This is not an easy read. This book will take patience, ambition, and perseverence to read. It&apos;s worth </span>
  <span id="freeText17294842629949216462" style="display:none">Maybe this will make me look stupid... but this book was far too brainy, academic and philosophical to be a really engrossing read. I had to make myself slog through certain portions of this book -- Eco is clearly brilliant, but needs to learn to keep a plot together. Too much extraneous information, too many digressions, too much detailed background information, and you distract from the plot.<br /><br />This is not an easy read. This book will take patience, ambition, and perseverence to read. It's worth it to some, but me? Even though the plot is good once it's all laid out and unraveled, I still kind of wish I had never bothered. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17294842629949216462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

